  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Preventing Sexual Violence in Burundi _ DH</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main activities:
1. Develop radio programs that will be broadcast on local radios
2. Training of religious leaders to incooperate sexual violence messages in their faith messages 
3. Set up clubs and train primary and secondary school teachers on sexual violence issues
4. Organize national stakeholders forum where sexual violence issues are discussed and seek ways of enforcing new legislations
5. Advocacy materials/messages developed to ensure that the commune have some budget to support sexual violence survivors
6. Training of members of existing community structures that traditionally deal with disputes in communities</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will incorperate lessons from the previous project and increase impact by sustaining the Sexual Violence (SV) messages in communities. The project will build on the achievement of the preceding FCO funded project by expanding geographically and reinforcing messages in areas already covered. The project will seek  to increase awareness and knowledge of the general population to prevent, protect and respond to sexual violence in communities targeted and beyond, with a focus of sensitizing communities on the newly enacted Burundi sexual violence law and other related legislation. This willl be done through the media, workshops and rallies. Secondly, the project will seek to increase access to holistic assistance to survivors of SV including access to justice.</narrative>
  </description>
